This is where our story of adventure started. Our story of a tea merchant named Norman Harper Bell, who in 1898, explored the world to create a tea distinctly for the country he called home. An original. A New Zealand tea. Our Bell tea. A tea that even those who watch their caffeine intake shouldn't have to miss out on. So we created Bell Decaf, with all the flavour of Bell Original but without the caffeine. Today our tea master blender still searches the world, bringing the best teas home to blend here, driven by that same spirit and curiosity for being the best at what we do, without compromise. To be original. It's the way we do things around here. So let's raise a cup, a mug, a recycled jam jar, to the robust and refreshingly honest tea that knows New Zealand.
